Burma VJ: Reporting From a Closed Country;;91;;97;;NC;;Thousands of citizens of Myanmar take to the streets in several cities to protest the Asian nation's repressive regime. The protests take on a new degree of seriousness when dozens of monks launch their own marches down city streets. This documentary from Anders Ostergaard focuses on the work of videographers and citizen journalists who defy the government's crackdown on the media -- a brave bunch who manage to transmit footage of the uprising to the outside world.;;Documentary;;Anders Ã˜stergaard;;2008;;George W. Bush;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/burma-vj